section.section:
Subject to paragraph (2) of this subsection, a retiree, or a beneficiary of a retiree, who retires on or before June 30, 1999 with a service retirement allowance, shall receive an annual retirement allowance adjustment as of July 1, 1999, as follows:
for a retiree who has been retired not more than 5 years, $1,200;
for a retiree who has been retired more than 5 years but not more than 10 years, $1,500;
for a retiree who has been retired more than 10 years but not more than 15 years, $1,800; and
for a retiree who has been retired more than 15 years, $2,100.
